No. 1925,

Misc.

Brady v. United States. Solicitor General Griswold, Assistant Attorney General Wilson, and Jerome M. Feit for the United States.

C. A. 10th Cir. Motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis granted. Certiorari granted. Case transferred to appellate docket and set for oral argument immediately following No. 1064 [394 U. S. 956].
